olds with additional scenes, quests, and challenges, gradually revealing the story of the fractured memory and the father\'s journey to reunite with his lost family on the mysterious island.*Scene 1: Family Vacation - Loading Luggage*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n[Quotation Box: "They are going for a trip on a yacht on a vacation, the scene starts with them quickly moving from the house and filling the bonnet of the van with the luggage.The family, consisting of a father, a mother, a son, and a daughter, hustles around the front yard, packing suitcases into the back of a spacious van.---\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n*Scene 7: Fractured Memories - Reminiscing the Past*\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n*Description:*\r\n\r\nThe father, surrounded by his makeshift family, reflects on fragments of memories.', 0, 'draftdocx', '2024-01-31 02:22:02', '2024-02-09 19:58:54'),
	(13, 2, '103_2065923_ProfessionalismReport.pdf', 197596, 'application/pdf', ' \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n  \r\nProject and Professionalism  \r\n(6CS007)  \r\n \r\nProfessionalism Report  \r\nBook your Barber  \r\nStudent Id    : 2065 923  \r\nStudent Name   : Madan Khanal  \r\nGroup     : L6CG1  \r\nSupervisor       : Mr. Nuraj Raj Bhandari  \r\nReader                        : Mr. Akash Adhikari  \r\nWord Count    :  \r\n \r\n  \r\n \r\nContents  \r\n1. Social Impact  ................................ ................................ ................................ ............  1 \r\n1.1.  Beneficial Aspect  ................................ ................................ ................................  1 \r\n1.2.  Detrimental Aspect  ................................ ................................ .............................  1 \r\n2. Ethical Issues ................................ ................................ ................................ ............  2 \r\n2.1.  Privacy Concerns  ................................ ................................ ...............................  2 \r\n2.2.  Fair Access  ................................ ................................ ................................ ........  3 \r\n3. Legal Implications  ................................ ................................ ................................ ..... 3 \r\n3.1.  GDPR Compliance  ................................ ................................ .............................  3 \r\n3.2.  Equity Act and Accessibility ................................ ................................ ................  4 \r\n4. Security Aspects  ................................ ................................ ................................ ....... 5 \r\n4.1.  Personal Data Protection  ................................ ................................ ...................  5 \r\n4.2.  Encryption  ................................ ................................ ................................ ..........  5 \r\nReferences  ................................ ................................ ................................ ......................  6 \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n \r\n 1 \r\n \r\n1. Social Impact  \r\nThe social impact of the Barber Appointment System is substantial, influencing both the \r\nservice providers and the customers.  \r\n1.1. Beneficial  Aspect  \r\nThe barber appointment system changes how customers feel when they visit. Instead of \r\nwaiting around, people can now pick the time they want to come in for a haircut. This \r\nmakes folks happy because they can plan when to visit and don\'t have to wait a long t ime. \r\nIt\'s like having control over their own schedule, which makes them feel good when they\'re \r\nat the barber shop. But it\'s not just good for customers. Barbers also benefit from this \r\nsystem. It helps them manage their time better, so they can focus more o n giving great \r\nhaircuts instead of worrying about too many people waiting. This makes customers even \r\nhappier because they get better service, and it might make them tell their friends about it \r\ntoo. \r\nThis system doesn\'t just fix waiting times; it makes things more reliable and professional. \r\nCustomers like knowing exactly when they\'ll get their haircut without any long waits. And \r\nfor barbers, it helps build their reputation as pros who care about being on time and \r\nmaking customers happy. When both customers and barbers feel good about the system, \r\nit makes the barber shop a nicer place for everyone. It\'s a win -win situation that helps the \r\nquality of service and how much customers enjoy their visit.  \r\n1.2. Detrimental  Aspect  \r\nIntroducing a system where you book your barber appointment can bring some good \r\nthings, but it also has downsides that might cause some problems. One big worry is that \r\nnot everyone might be able to use it. Some folks might not have computers or might not \r\nknow how to book online, which might make it hard for them to get a haircut when they \r\nwant. This could make a gap between people who can easily book online and those who \r\nprefer just showing up at the shop. For some, going in without an appointment is how th ey \r\nlike it or the only way they can get their haircut. Also, using this system a lot might change \r\nthe way barbers and customers talk and get along. Usually, when you just walk in for a \r\nhaircut, there\'s chatting and a friendly vibe between barbers and custo mers. But if most 2 \r\n \r\npeople start looking ahead, it might take away that casual and friendly feeling. The system \r\nhelps the barbers manage time better, but it might mean less of those fun, unplanned \r\nconversations that make the barber shop feel special.  \r\nAnother problem is that this system might not work well for people who come in without \r\nan appointment. If the schedule is always full, those who donâ€™t book beforehand might \r\nhave to wait longer or might even get turned away. This could make them upset and l ess \r\nlikely to come back. Plus, the barber shop might lose money because theyâ€™re not helping \r\nthese customers as well as they could. Itâ€™s important to find a balance between the good \r\nthings the appointment system brings and making sure everyone can still eas ily get a \r\nhaircut. Keeping things flexible and allowing people to walk in without an appointment is \r\nimportant to keep the friendly vibe and make sure everyone feels welcome. Making sure \r\nthe system doesnâ€™t take away from the special connections between barb ers and \r\ncustomers will help keep the barber shop a great place for everyone.  \r\n2. Ethical Issues  \r\nEthical concerns in the Barber Appointment System include the issue related to user \r\nprivacy, data security, and fair access to services.  \r\n2.1. Privacy Concerns  \r\nWhen you make an appointment at a barber shop, you share info like your name, phone \r\nnumber, and sometimes payment details. But there\'s a worry that this info might not be \r\nsafe if the system isn\'t secure enough. You might wonder what they do with your info,  like \r\nwhen you visit the barber shop. If they share it without asking, it can make you feel \r\nuneasy. It\'s important they keep your details safe and donâ€™t use them without your \r\npermission. This is about keeping your personal info private and secure. It\'s sup er \r\nimportant that the barber shop does things the right way with your info. They should ask \r\nfor your permission before taking any details and be clear about how they\'ll use and \r\nprotect your info. Itâ€™s all about earning your trust and handling your info car efully.  \r\nItâ€™s not just about hackers trying to get your data; itâ€™s also about how the barber shop itself \r\ntakes care of it. If they donâ€™t follow the rules or arenâ€™t careful enough, your private details \r\ncould end up where they shouldnâ€™t be. This might lead to problem s like someone 3 \r\n \r\npretending to be you or getting ads you don\'t want. To stop these problems, the system \r\nneeds to be super safe from hackers. They should have clear rules about how they collect, \r\nstore, and use your data. And if you ever want them to get rid of your info, th ey should do \r\nit without any trouble. Making sure they handle your personal info the right way is crucial \r\nfor keeping your trust and keeping your private stuff safe.  \r\n2.2. Fair Access  \r\nMaking sure everyone can easily get a haircut is a big part of being fair with a barber \r\nappointment system. It\'s not just about keeping information safe; it\'s also about treating \r\neveryone equally and giving them the same chances to get a haircut. Some folk s like to \r\nplan and book their haircut time using computers or phones. But not everyone can do \r\nthat. Some people might not have these gadgets or might need a haircut right away \r\nbecause something unexpected happened. Being fair means making a system that wor ks \r\nfor both types of people,  those who plan and those who show up without an appointment. \r\nIt\'s like finding a way to make sure everyone, no matter how they like to book their haircut, \r\ncan still get it done when they need it.  \r\nThe goal is to make sure nobody feels left out. If the system only helps those who book \r\nahead, it might leave out folks who can\'t do that. So, it\'s important to have a system that\'s \r\nfriendly to both planned appointments and people who just walk in. This fa irness stops \r\nany unfair treatment in the barber shop. If the system only helps those who book ahead, \r\nit might not be fair to those who need to walk in without an appointment for different \r\nreasons. So, having a fair system means creating a place where every one feels welcome \r\nand gets the same chance to get a great haircut, no matter how they decide to book their \r\nappointments.  \r\n3. Legal Implications  \r\nThe legal landscape for the Barber Appointment System involves adherence to cyber \r\nlaws, such as GDPT, Equity Act, and copyright issues.  \r\n3.1. GDPR Compliance  \r\nThe GDPR is like a set of rules that tell companies how to handle your personal info. For \r\nthe barber system, it means they must be careful with your details. They canâ€™t just take 4 \r\n \r\nyour info; they need your permission first. And when they use it, it\'s only for booking your \r\nhaircut, nothing else. It\'s like they must keep it safe and locked up, and they canâ€™t let \r\nanyone else use it unless you say it\'s okay. If you want them to delete y our info, they must \r\ndo it. Following these rules ensures the system keeps your private info safe and respects \r\nyour wishes. Not following these rules is serious. They could get in trouble and face big \r\nfines. The rules are there to protect your info, like a shield making sure it stays safe and \r\nisnâ€™t used in ways you didnâ€™t agree to  (Zaeem & Barber, 2020) . \r\nGDPR keeps your privacy safe. When the barber system follows these rules, it shows \r\nthey care about your info. Itâ€™s important because your info should only be used the way \r\nyou want it to be. It\'s like putting a lock on your details to keep them safe and how  you \r\nwant them to be used.  \r\n3.2. Equity Act and Accessibility  \r\nFollowing the Equity Act for a barber appointment system means making it friendly for \r\neveryone, no matter what makes them different. It\'s like setting up the system so that \r\neveryone, including those with disabilities, can use it easily without any problems . This \r\nmight mean using special tools for those who canâ€™t see well, like things that read the \r\nscreen out loud. Or for folks who find it hard to move their hands, making the buttons \r\nbigger or easier to use. Imagine someone who can\'t see well trying to book a haircut. The \r\nsystem should talk or read whatâ€™s on the screen so they understand and can book their \r\nhaircut without any trouble. And for someone who can\'t move their hands easily, they \r\nmight need buttons that are easier to touch or a simpler way to move a round the system.  \r\nNot everyone can use computers or phones to book appointments. Some people might \r\nwant to call or just walk in without an appointment. So, following the Equity Act means \r\nmaking sure the system isnâ€™t only for tech -savvy folks. It\'s about making a fair system  that \r\nworks for everyone, so anyone in the community can easily book a haircut in their own \r\nway. When the system follows the Equity Act, it\'s like giving a big welcome to everyone, \r\nno matter what they\'re good at or how they use technology. It makes sure no body feels \r\nleft out or has trouble using the system. Itâ€™s all about being fair and making it easy for \r\neveryone to get the service they need  (Congressional Research Service, 2021) . 5 \r\n \r\n4. Security Aspects  \r\nSecurity is paramount in the Barber Appointment System, focusing on the protection of \r\npersonal data, encryption, and overall user wellbeing.  \r\n4.1. Personal Data Protection  \r\nProtecting personal information in a barber appointment system, like names and phone \r\nnumbers, is super important. It\'s like locking these details in a safe box so only trusted \r\nfolks can get to them. To do this, the system needs strong security to stop anyo ne \r\nsneaking in and taking this important info. There are strict rules for handling this info. The \r\nsystem must follow these rules on how it collects, stores, and uses data. People trust the \r\nsystem to keep their info private, so having tough protection is ke y. It\'s like making a \r\nstrong fort to keep this info safe and secret.  \r\nImagine giving you your phone number to book a haircut. You expect it to stay safe and \r\nnot be used without your say so. That\'s why top -notch security in the system is a must. \r\nItâ€™s all about taking care of your details and keeping them away from the wrong p eople. \r\nWithout strong safety, this info could be at risk from hackers. It\'s like leaving the door \r\nopen for someone to sneak in and take something important. This could lead to big \r\nproblems like someone stealing your identity or misusing your info.  \r\n4.2. Encryption  \r\nIn a barber appointment system, encryption is like turning your important info into a secret \r\ncode that only trusted people can understand. It\'s like locking your data in a special box \r\nwith a code that only the right folks have. This makes it hard for sneak y people or hackers \r\nto understand or use your info if they try to get it, keeping it safe.  \r\nUsing encryption is super important because it adds a strong layer of protection to your \r\npersonal details, almost like putting a super strong lock on a door. Even if someone tries \r\nto sneak in and take your info, they won\'t be able to understand it because it\'s in a secret \r\ncode. This helps stop cyber troubles or people trying to steal your info. Encryption is all \r\nabout keeping your personal info safe and secret in the system. It\'s like making a secret \r\ncode that only the trusted people can understand, so no o ne else can see your info or \r\ncause any online problems  (Bai, et al., 2020) . 6 \r\n \r\nReferences  \r\nBai, W., Pearson, M., Kelley, P. & Mazurek, M., 2020. Improving Non -Experts\' \r\nUnderstanding of End -to-End Encryption: An Exploratory Study. Maryland, European \r\nWorkshop on Usable Security.  \r\nCongressional Research Service, 2021. The Digital Equity Act of 2021. [Online]  \r\nAvailable at: https://crsreports.congress.gov/product/pdf/IF/IF11901/1  \r\n[Accessed 2 December 2023].  \r\nZaeem, R. N. & Barber, K. S., 2020. The Effect of the GDPR on Privacy Policies: Recent \r\nProgress and Future Promise. ACM Transactions on Management Information Systems, \r\nVolume 12.  \r\n \r\n \r\n ', 'Barber appointment system changes how customers feel when they visit. Instead of waiting around, people can now pick the time they want to come in for a haircut. Barbers also benefit from this system, so they can focus more o n giving great haircuts instead of worrying about too many people waiting.', 0, '103_2065923_professionalismreportpdf', '2024-01-31 09:59:16', '2024-02-09 19:58:54'),
	(14, 2, 'SupCode_2065923_Literature_Review.docx', 90705, 'application/vnd.openxmlformats-officedocument.wordprocessingml.document', 'Project and Professionalism\r\n\r\n(6CS007)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLiterature Review\r\n\r\nBook Your Barber\r\n\r\nProject and Professionalism\r\n\r\n(6CS007)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nLiterature Review\r\n\r\nBook Your Barber\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nStudent Id			: 2065923\r\n\r\nStudent Name		: Madan Khanal\r\n\r\nGroup				: L6CG1\r\n\r\nSupervisor     		: Mr. Nuraj Rajbhandari\r\n\r\nReader                        : Mr. Akash Adhikari\r\n\r\nWord Count			: 3088\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nStudent Id			: 2065923\r\n\r\nStudent Name		: Madan Khanal\r\n\r\nGroup				: L6CG1\r\n\r\nSupervisor     		: Mr. Nuraj Rajbhandari\r\n\r\nReader                        : Mr. Akash Adhikari\r\n\r\nWord Count			: 3088\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTable of Contents\r\n\r\n		1.	Smart College Event Management System: A Web-Based Approach	1\r\n\r\n	Introduction	1\r\n\r\n	Problem	1\r\n\r\n	How It Works	1\r\n\r\n	Features	1\r\n\r\n	Technology	2\r\n\r\n	Results and Future Plans	2\r\n\r\n	Conclusion	2\r\n\r\n		2.	Membership information system Using Node JS	3\r\n\r\n		3.	Exploring user acceptance of medical e-appointment systems for mental healthcare: A systematic literature review	5\r\n\r\n	Introduction	5\r\n\r\n	Article Mapping	5\r\n\r\n	Methods	6\r\n\r\n	Results	6\r\n\r\n	Prevailing Technology Adoption Models and Theories	6\r\n\r\n	Determinants of MEAS Acceptance	6\r\n\r\n	Deployment of MEAS	6\r\n\r\n	Discussion	7\r\n\r\n	Conclusions	7\r\n\r\n		4.	Improving Healthcare with Online Doctor Appointments: A Case Study of Nkozi Hospital	8\r\n\r\n	Introduction	8\r\n\r\n	Methodology	8\r\n\r\n	Tools and Technology	9\r\n\r\n	Testing and Implementation	9\r\n\r\n	Conclusion	9\r\n\r\n		5.	Creating a Better Appointment System for Schools	10\r\n\r\n	Introduction:	10\r\n\r\n	Methodology	10\r\n\r\n	Testing and Implementation	10\r\n\r\n	Results and Conclusion	10\r\n\r\n	References	12\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nSmart College Event Management System: A Web-Based Approach\r\n\r\nIntroduction\r\n\r\nCollege events are important for students, helping them learn and connect with each other. But as events increase, it\'s tough to manage all the details. Using papers and spreadsheets isn\'t enough anymore. So, we made a Smart College Event Management System using the internet. This system makes event planning easier, keeps data organized, and helps everyone work together better (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\nProblem\r\n\r\nColleges use old-fashioned ways to manage events, which isn\'t very efficient. To solve this, we made the Smart College Event Management System. It\'s a website where all event information is kept in one place. It\'s like a central hub for everything related to events. Anyone can use it from anywhere (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\nHow It Works\r\n\r\nOur system uses a special combination of technologies known as the MERN stack. It\'s like a powerful toolbox for making websites. MongoDB is used to store data, like event details. Express.js helps the back-end work, while React.js makes the front-end look nice and interactive. And Node.js runs everything smoothly (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\nFeatures\r\n\r\nAdmins can create, edit, and delete events.\r\n\r\nThey can also manage volunteers and track attendance.\r\n\r\nUsers can see event info, register, and log in.\r\n\r\nEvent details, location, time, and fees are easy to find.\r\n\r\nUsers can even sign up to help at events.\r\n\r\nRegistration:\r\n\r\nBefore using the system, you need to sign up.\r\n\r\nThis process makes sure you\'re authorized to use it.\r\n\r\nAdministrators:\r\n\r\nAdmins have special powers to control events.\r\n\r\nThey can create, edit, and manage events easily.\r\n\r\nThey also oversee how events are going.\r\n\r\nUsers:\r\n\r\nRegular users can see event details and register.\r\n\r\nThey can also volunteer and track their attendance.\r\n\r\nTechnology\r\n\r\nWe used HTML, CSS, and JavaScript to create an engaging website. The MERN stack made everything work together smoothly (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\nResults and Future Plans\r\n\r\nOur system makes event planning and management much simpler. It saves time and effort, making events run smoothly. We might even make mobile apps and connect with different devices in the future (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n\r\nOur Smart College Event Management System is a big step forward in organizing college events. It uses modern web tools and the MERN stack to make things easy for everyone. It\'s not just about events â€“ it also helps with attendance, volunteers, and sharing information. This system makes college events more organized, efficient, and enjoyable for everyone involved (Pansare, Patil, Patil, Patil, & Bhonde, 2023).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMembership information system Using Node JS\r\n\r\nIn the world of organizing membership-related activities, making sure that we handle member data efficiently and accurately is super important. This involves managing and creating data about the people who are part of these memberships, organizing activity schedules, and dealing with their finances. In this study, we explore using Node.js, a computer language, to create a system that helps us manage all this membership information. To make sure our system is well-organized and does what it\'s supposed to do, we use a design method called the Unified Modeling Language (UML). What we found is that Node.js is good at creating systems for memberships. This system, overseen by an administrator, does a lot of things well. It collects and organizes data about members, manages their money, keeps track of what activities they\'re involved in, and handles any contributions they make. This system is super-efficient and keeps a detailed history of everything members do, like when they first sign up, when they make updates, when they log in, when they make financial transactions, donate money, and participate in activities. Based on our findings, we have some suggestions for making this membership management system even better. We recommend adding a notification feature to help people access the information they need more easily. It would also be a good idea to create a version of the system that works well on mobile devices. In summary, the important terms related to this study are Membership System, Information System, Node.js, and Adonis.js (Sihotang, et al., 2019)..\r\n\r\nTechnology has been advancing fast, and this has led to a lot of research to find flexible solutions for different kinds of business processes in many industries. One area where technology plays a big role is in web services that give people information in an easy-to-use way. Information systems are a big part of managing everyday business transactions, helping with day-to-day operations, and giving important reports to people outside the organization. One specific use of information systems is in managing memberships. These systems help with things like signing up new members, handling their money, keeping track of what they do, and managing contributions and donations. Web-based systems are crucial because they help process data quickly and accurately, making work more efficient. In this research, we followed a structured approach called the Waterfall method. It\'s a systematic and step-by-step way of developing software. It\'s been around for a long time and is widely used in software engineering, even though some people say it\'s old-fashioned. The key idea is that each step must be completed before moving on to the next one, like a waterfall flowing down. We also used a method called Business Process Engineering to redesign existing business processes to match what our system needs. These processes include things like signing up new members, activating their accounts, managing their money, handling refunds, dealing with donations, and managing contacts (Sihotang, et al., 2019).\r\n\r\nTo build our system, we needed the right tools. We used a computer with Windows 10, a local database server called MariaDB, a text editor called Visual Studio Code, and Node.js as the main programming language. We also used Adonis.js, which is built on Node.js, to make our system even better.\r\n\r\nFollowing the Waterfall method, we successfully created a web-based membership information system using Node.js. We divided our research findings into two parts: the design of the system and how well it worked, which we tested and evaluated. In summary, this research explores how to make a membership information system using Node.js and a structured approach. The system efficiently manages member data, financial records, activities, and contributions, and there\'s potential to make it even better with features like notifications and a mobile version (Sihotang, et al., 2019).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nExploring user acceptance of medical e-appointment systems for mental healthcare: A systematic literature review\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis study explores how people use online systems to make doctor appointments for mental health services. These systems promise to make scheduling appointments easier and more efficient. However, not much research has been done on whether people like and use these systems, especially in Morocco. We analyzed 11 studies conducted between 2012 and 2023 that used technology acceptance models. The most common models used were the Technology Acceptance Model (TAM) and the Continuance Intention of Use Model. We found 35 factors that influence whether people accept and use these systems, including how good the system is, how easy it is to use, and how much they trust it. Interestingly, there\'s very little research on this topic in African mental healthcare, which is something that future studies should explore.\r\n\r\nIntroduction\r\n\r\nTechnology is changing the way we access healthcare, including making appointments with doctors online. These online systems, called Medical E-Appointment Systems (MEAS), are supposed to make it easier for people to see their mental health providers. They can help reduce the time people spend waiting for appointments and reduce the chances of missing them. However, not many studies have looked at whether people like using these systems, especially in Morocco. Most studies focus on how well these systems work and how they affect healthcare services. This review aims to fill this gap by examining 11 studies published between 2012 and 2023 that use technology acceptance models to understand MEAS use (Khalil & Serhier, 2023)..\r\n\r\nArticle Mapping\r\n\r\nIn this review, we will talk about the models and theories that researchers use to study how people use MEAS. We\'ll also look at the factors that influence whether someone likes and uses these systems. We\'ll discuss where these studies were done, who the participants were, and what the studies found. Finally, we\'ll suggest areas for future research.\r\n\r\nMethods\r\n\r\nTo find the studies we reviewed, we followed specific guidelines and searched for articles from November 2022 to April 2023. We used four databases: Web of Science, Science Direct, PubMed, and Google Scholar. We used keywords like "Technology Adoption," "Healthcare," "Mental Health," "E-Appointment System," and others. We only looked at studies published between 2012 and 2023 that used technology adoption models to study MEAS use.\r\n\r\nResults\r\n\r\nWe started with 805 studies in our search but narrowed it down to 11 studies after removing duplicates and checking titles and abstracts.\r\n\r\nPrevailing Technology Adoption Models and Theories\r\n\r\nWe found two main categories of models used to understand MEAS use. The first one is the Technology Acceptance Model (TAM) and its variations, used in four studies. The second category is post-technology adoption models, used in three studies. Some studies combined TAM with other theories like trust theory and innovation diffusion theory. One study used the Unified Theory of Acceptance and Use of Technology (UTAUT) and its variations.\r\n\r\nDeterminants of MEAS Acceptance\r\n\r\nIn our review, we found 35 factors that influence whether someone accepts and uses MEAS. One common factor is "behavioral intention," which means whether someone plans to use MEAS. Many studies looked at TAM factors like how easy it is to use (perceived ease of use) and how useful it is (perceived usefulness). Other factors include service quality, satisfaction, user experience, relationship quality, and system quality. Some factors were specific to the context of the study and not part of any existing technology acceptance theory.\r\n\r\nDeployment of MEAS\r\n\r\nMost of the studies we reviewed focused on general medical services, not just mental healthcare. Only one study looked at MEAS for blood donation, and another studied MEAS in nutrition.\r\n\r\nDiscussion\r\n\r\nOur review helps us understand how people use MEAS for mental healthcare. Most studies extended the TAM model to see if people intend to use or continue using MEAS. We suggest that future research should explore different models, like the theory of health beliefs. "Behavioral intention" emerged as an important factor in MEAS use, like other research in healthcare. TAM factors like perceived ease of use and perceived usefulness were crucial in deciding whether people accept MEAS. Other factors like satisfaction, trust, and user experience also influenced people\'s intentions to use MEAS (Khalil & Serhier, 2023).\r\n\r\nConclusions\r\n\r\nOur review found a gap in research about MEAS use in African mental healthcare, particularly from the perspective of healthcare providers. TAM and its variations, along with the Continuance Intention of Use Model, are the most used models to study MEAS use. We identified 35 factors that influence MEAS acceptance, including internal factors related to users\' beliefs and perceptions. These factors play a big role in how people use MEAS. Key factors include the quality of the healthcare service, the quality of the system, effective communication, perceived usefulness, ease of use, satisfaction, and trust. This study gives valuable insights into technology acceptance in healthcare and suggests areas for future research in mental healthcare settings (Khalil & Serhier, 2023).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nImproving Healthcare with Online Doctor Appointments: A Case Study of Nkozi Hospital\r\n\r\nThis study conducted at Nkozi Hospital shows how using computers to manage hospital information can help with the challenges of a growing population. Before, they used a manual system, which caused problems like losing data and people getting access to information they shouldn\'t. To fix these issues, they made an Online Doctor Appointment System. They collected data using surveys, interviews, and watching how things work. They used a program called SPSS to analyze the data and put it in tables and charts. They built the system using a database called MySQL and a program called Dreamweaver. They also tested it before using it for real. The study suggests keeping the system up to date and training staff to use it better.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIntroduction\r\n\r\nThis part talks about how Nkozi Hospital started using an online system to book doctor appointments instead of the old manual way. It says that using technology like this is important, especially in Africa where more and more people are using technology. The study aims to fix problems with the old system, like patients waiting a long time and staff having too much work. It also mentions that having an online system is important during the COVID-19 pandemic.\r\n\r\nThe study has three main goals: to learn from what others have done before, to design the new system, and to test it. They want to find out what problems the old system had, how to make the new one, and how to check if it works. The study only looks at Nkozi Hospital, and its goal is to make things faster and better for patients. This study is important because it can help make healthcare better, guide decisions, and teach others about healthcare, technology, and how they affect society (Davis & Kabega, 2023)..\r\n\r\nMethodology\r\n\r\nIn this part, the researcher talks about how they collected information for the online doctor appointment system study. They used two kinds of methods: numbers and words. Numbers helped them see the big picture, and words helped them understand the details. They talked to different people like doctors, patients, and nurses to make sure they got a good mix of opinions.\r\n\r\nTo collect data, they used surveys, interviews, watching what happened, and looking at records. Surveys are like questionnaires, where people answer questions on paper or online. Interviews are when you talk to someone and ask them questions to get more information. Watching what happened is when you quietly watch people and write down what they do. Looking at records is when you read documents to learn more.\r\n\r\nAfter collecting data, they looked at it with a computer program called SPSS. This program changed the data into percentages and put it in tables and charts. This helped them see what was wrong with the old system and how to make it better.\r\n\r\nOverall, this part explains how they gathered and studied the information for the online doctor appointment system study (Davis & Kabega, 2023)..\r\n\r\nTools and Technology\r\n\r\nTo make the online system, they needed a good computer with a special database program and some other tools. They used a web browser and PHP to talk to the database. They also used things like SQL server, JavaScript, HTML, CSS, Dreamweaver, and Windows. All these things worked together to make sure everything ran smoothly.\r\n\r\nTesting and Implementation\r\n\r\nBefore the online system was ready to use, they needed to make sure it worked correctly. They tested it on different types of computers, like Windows and Linux. They checked each part of the system by itself to make sure it worked right. Then, they put all the parts together and tested how they worked together.\r\n\r\nAfter the testing, they started using the system for real. This included installing it, changing from the old system to the new one, teaching people how to use it, and making it available for everyone to use.\r\n\r\nConclusion\r\n\r\nThe new online doctor appointment system at Nkozi Hospital will make healthcare better by improving the way things are done. In the past, they did a lot of things by hand, which made treatment slower and less effective. But now, with the new system, things will be faster and smoother. It will help more patients get the care they need without long waits and hassles. In summary, the new system will modernize and improve healthcare at Nkozi Hospital, and it fits with the trend of using technology to make healthcare better (Davis & Kabega, 2023).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCreating a Better Appointment System for Schools\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMore and more people are using the internet to book appointments these days. Businesses are using online systems to make scheduling easier. This paper talks about making a special online system just for schools, especially for students and their teachers. This system is designed to make appointment scheduling automatic, reduce mistakes, and make things run more smoothly. We explained how we made this system and checked if it works well. We also talked about the technology we used and the important design choices we made (Qaffas & Barker, 2012)..\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIntroduction:\r\n\r\nWe all use web applications every day, like apps on our phones or websites on our computers. These apps have made many tasks much easier. One area where web apps can be helpful is in scheduling appointments, especially in schools. In the past, schools used manual methods for scheduling appointments, which often led to problems like double bookings or missed appointments. This paper is about creating an online appointment system to solve these issues.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThe goal of our system is to make it easy for students to book appointments with their teachers. It works in real-time, meaning appointments are scheduled instantly without errors. It\'s available 24/7, making it convenient for both students and teachers.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nMethodology\r\n\r\nTo build the system, we designed a user-friendly interface and added features that students and teachers need. We carefully thought about the data the system would use and created the system\'s structure accordingly. The main functions of the system include user registration, managing student projects, scheduling appointments, confirming appointments, and canceling appointments.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTesting and Implementation\r\n\r\nWe tested the system thoroughly to make sure it works correctly and is reliable. This testing included checking how users navigate the system, registering as a user, managing student projects, scheduling appointments, receiving email notifications, and managing user access. The system\'s ability to send email reminders for appointments was an important feature we checked. We also gathered feedback from users to understand what they found important.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nResults and Conclusion\r\n\r\nWe conducted a survey with 28 students to get their feedback on the system. Most of them were studying for a master\'s degree. The survey showed that students found the system useful, especially the ability to join projects with teachers and the importance of email reminders for appointments. The system we developed has the potential to make appointment scheduling in schools much more efficient and accurate.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nIn summary, using web-based appointment systems in schools can modernize and simplify appointment processes, benefiting both students and teachers. This paper contributes to the growing field of web applications and their role in making administrative tasks in education easier (Qaffas & Barker, 2012).\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nReferences\r\n\r\nDavis, M. & Kabega, 2023. Online doctor appointment system by kabega davis mayiga. s.l.:s.n.\r\n\r\nKhalil, L. & Serhier, Z., 2023. Exploring user acceptance of medical e-appointment systems for mental healthcare: A systematic literature review. SHS Web of Conferences, Volume 175.\r\n\r\nPansare, A. et al., 2023. Smart College Event Management System Using MERN Stack. [Online] \r\nAvailable at: https://www.ijraset.com/research-paper/smart-college-event-management-system-using-mern-stack\r\n\r\nQaffas, A. & Barker, T., 2012. Online Appointment Management System. \r\n\r\nSihotang, J., Pakpahan, A. & Yousa, R., 2019. Membership Information System Using Node JS. Abstract Proceedings International Scholars Conference, Volume 7, pp. 1841-1852.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n2', 'Overall, this part explains how they gathered and studied the information for the online doctor appointment system study (Davis & Kabega, 2023)..\r\n\r\nTools and Technology\r\n\r\nTo make the online system, they needed a good computer with a special database program and some other tools.Exploring user acceptance of medical e-app