	(21, 2, 'Day 06 Social Media Marketing.pdf', 95986, 'application/pdf', 'Day 6: LinkedIn Basics and\nProfile OptimizationDS-SMM-B01-D06Visit LinkedIn Website\nGo to www.linkedin.com to start the account creation process.\nClick "Join Now":\nLocate and click on the "Join Now" button to initiate the sign-up.\nComplete Basic Information\nEnter essential details like your name, email, and password.\nEnsure accuracy for a professional and credible profile.\nProfile Photo Upload\nAdd a professional and clear profile picture.\nHighlight the significance of a visually appealing photo.Creating a LinkedIn AccountDS-SMM-B01-D06Headline and Summary\nCraft a compelling headline that reflects professional identity.\nWrite a concise and impactful summary to introduce yourself.\nEducation and Work Experience\nInput relevant education and work details.\nEmphasize showcasing achievements and responsibilities.\nSkills and Recommendations\nAdd skills that align with your professional expertise.\nSeek recommendations from colleagues or supervisors.Creating a LinkedIn AccountDS-SMM-B01-D06Accurate and Up-to-Date Information\nStress the importance of providing accurate and current details.\nExplain how this information forms the foundation of a strong professional\nstart.ImportanceDS-SMM-B01-D06Essential Elements\nCompelling Headline\nThe professional tagline displayed below your name.\nCaptures attention and communicates professional identity.\nActs as a quick snapshot of expertise and aspirations.\nImpactful Summary\nA concise and engaging overview of your professional journey.\nProvides a deeper insight into skills, achievements, and career goals.\nEncourages connections by showcasing personality and passion.Building an Optimized LinkedIn ProfileDS-SMM-B01-D06Experience Section\nDetailed information about your work history and accomplishments.\nAllows others to understand your professional journey.\nHighlights expertise, responsibilities, and achievements.Building an Optimized LinkedIn ProfileDS-SMM-B01-D06Keywords and Skills\nStrategically include relevant keywords for searchability.\nShowcase a diverse set of skills to encompass professional strengths.\nProfessional Photo\nUse a high-quality and professional-looking profile picture.\nHighlight the importance of making a positive first impression.\nCustomized LinkedIn URL\nCreate a personalized LinkedIn URL for a professional touch.\nSimplifies sharing and enhances online visibility.Tips for OptimizationDS-SMM-B01-D06LinkedIn Connections\nLinkedIn Connections represent the individuals you are directly connected with\non the platform.\nFacilitates professional networking and relationship-building.\nBuilding Connections\nConnecting with Colleagues and Peers\nStrengthen professional relationships by connecting with colleagues,\nclassmates, and peers.\nNetworking Opportunities\nGain access to the networks of your connections, expanding potential\nopportunities.\nUtilize mutual connections for introductions and referrals.Understanding LinkedIn Connections and EndorsementsDS-SMM-B01-D06LinkedIn Endorsements\nEndorsements are a way for connections to validate and vouch for your skills\nand expertise.\nAdds credibility to profile by showcasing others\' acknowledgment.\nProvides a quick overview of your strengths and competencies.\nEndorsing and Being Endorsed\nEndorsing Others\nAcknowledge the skills of your connections by endorsing them.\nStrengthens professional relationships and fosters a supportive community.\nBeing Endorsed\nEncourage others to endorse your skills by showcasing your expertise.\nRegularly update your skills section for relevant endorsements.Understanding LinkedIn Connections and EndorsementsDS-SMM-B01-D06AssignmentDS-SMM-B01-D06\nOptimize a LinkedIn Profile\nOptimize a LinkedIn profile with a focus on professional branding.\nEmphasize the practical application by integrating concepts learned during the session.DhanyawaadDS-SMM-B01-D06\nAny Question?', NULL, 0, 'day-06-social-media-marketingpdf', '2024-02-01 13:03:03', '2024-02-09 19:58:54'),
